      <bioghist>
         <head>Historical Information</head>
         <p>Southampton County was formed in 1749 from Isle of Wight
         County. Part of Nansemond County was added in 1785.</p>
         <p>An act passed by the Virginia legislature in 1803 required
         every free negro or mulatto to be registered and numbered in a
         book to be kept by the county clerk. The register listed the
         age, name, color, stature, marks or scars, in what court the
         person was emancipated or whether the person was born free.
         Some clerks recorded additional information not required by
         the law.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>The volumes cover the years 1794-1864.</p>
